The paper deals with the concept of randomness and Kolmogorov complexity, which are central topics in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of the effectiveness of transforming sequences and strings, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concept of independence and linear dependency, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
